# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# agents/.gitignore
#
# Anything under agents/ that's regenerable from the scripts here.
# Paths in this file are relative to agents/. The layout is:
#
#   agents/HUB.html              entry-point (generated)
#   agents/packages/             agent code (mapper, critic, api-flow)
#   agents/tools/                build scripts (python + shell)
#   agents/data/                 every generated artifact
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ---------- agents/HUB.html ----------
#
# Always regenerate from tools/build-hub.py; never commit.

HUB.html

# ---------- agents/packages/ ----------
#
# TypeScript build outputs + npm artifacts for each agent package.

packages/*/dist/
packages/*/node_modules/
packages/*/*.tsbuildinfo

# ---------- agents/data/knowledge-graphs/ ----------
#
# Tracked:
#   <package>-module-level/MODULE_RELATIONSHIPS*.md (text Mermaid for diff/PR)
#
# Everything else is regenerable. Ignore every subdirectory by default,
# then re-include the *-module-level/ ones so the committed .md files
# inside are tracked.

data/knowledge-graphs/*/
!data/knowledge-graphs/*-module-level/

# Within those re-included dirs, ignore the generated HTML + per-run
# graphify-out/ subdir.
data/knowledge-graphs/*-module-level/*.html
data/knowledge-graphs/*-module-level/graphify-out/

# ---------- agents/data/codebase-map/ ----------
#
# *.md files are LLM-enriched narratives — tracked.
# *.json sidecars are regenerable from the mapper — ignored.

data/codebase-map/*.json

# ---------- agents/data/schema/ ----------
#
# Schema diagram is regenerated from backend/prisma/schema.prisma by
# tools/build-schema-diagram.py. No content here is hand-written.

data/schema/

# ---------- agents/data/critic-out/ ----------
#
# Per-run review artifacts (per-module markdown, synthesis, raw JSON
# sidecars, and the cross-run issue tracker). All regenerable.

data/critic-out/
